# Webinar Questions & Answers Feature

Admins should be able to attach questions to a webinar during creation (or editing). Enrolled users see those questions on the webinar detail page and can submit answers. Admins and faculty can view all submitted answers.

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Database — New Migration

#### [NEW] `supabase/migrations/20260428_webinar_questions.sql`

Two new tables:

| Table | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `session_questions` | Questions created by admin, linked to a session |
| `session_question_answers` | Answers submitted by enrolled users |

**`session_questions`**
```
id UUID PK
session_id UUID FK → sessions(id)
question_text TEXT NOT NULL
question_order INT DEFAULT 1
created_by UUID FK → profiles(id)
created_at TIMESTAMPTZ
updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ
```

**`session_question_answers`**
```
id UUID PK
question_id UUID FK → session_questions(id)
user_id UUID FK → profiles(id)
answer_text TEXT NOT NULL
created_at TIMESTAMPTZ
updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ
UNIQUE(question_id, user_id)   -- one answer per user per question
```

**RLS policies:**
- `session_questions`: Everyone can SELECT; only admin/faculty can INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE
- `session_question_answers`: Users can SELECT/INSERT/UPDATE their own answers; admins and faculty can SELECT all answers

---

### 2. API Routes

#### [NEW] `app/api/sessions/[id]/questions/route.ts`
- `GET` — Return all questions for a session (with answer count for admin/faculty, or user's own answer if user)
- `POST` — Admin-only: create a question for a session

#### [NEW] `app/api/sessions/[id]/questions/[questionId]/route.ts`
- `PATCH` — Admin-only: edit question text / order
- `DELETE` — Admin-only: delete a question

#### [NEW] `app/api/sessions/[id]/questions/[questionId]/answers/route.ts`
- `GET` — Admin/faculty only: get all answers for this question
- `POST` — Enrolled user: submit or update their answer

---

### 3. UI Components

#### [NEW] `components/sessions/WebinarQuestions.tsx`
A shared client component rendered on the webinar detail page. Adapts its display based on the current user role:
- **Admin/Faculty view:** "Questions" tab with a list of all questions, each expandable to show all user answers in a table
- **User view (enrolled):** A form per question where they can type and submit/update their answer

#### [NEW] `components/sessions/QuestionManager.tsx`
Admin-only sub-component embedded inside the **Create** and **Edit** webinar forms. Allows:
- Adding new questions (text input + "Add" button)
- Reordering questions (up/down arrows)
- Deleting questions

> [!NOTE]
> On the **Create** page, questions will be saved after the session is created (we get the session ID from the API response, then POST each question). This keeps the create flow clean without restructuring it.

